markdownRemark.html: The Giunta Press motto "Nil Candidius" reminds me of Giulio de' Medici's "Candor Illaesus." given that Bernardo spent time in Florence while Giulio was running the place (from Rome, via Cardinal Passerini et al.), might this be an intentional connection?
